  "body": "#### System information\r\nerigon version 2022.99.99-dev-2e4e7bd4\r\nOSX\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\ntrace_block should return a record indicating the miner even though there is no longer a miner's reward.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nThis curl command:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\", \"id\": 1, \"method\": \"trace_block\", \"params\": [\"0xedcde0\"]}' http://localhost:8545\r\n```\r\n\r\nreturns this result:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"id\": 1,\r\n  \"result\": []\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is a block with no transactions. The corresponding call to `eth_getBlockByNumber` returns conflicting information.\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\", \"id\": 1, \"method\": \"eth_getBlockByNumber\", \"params\": [\"0xedcde0\", true]}' http://localhost:8545\r\n```\r\n\r\nreturns:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"id\": 1,\r\n  \"result\": {\r\n    \"baseFeePerGas\": \"0x356959685\",\r\n    \"difficulty\": \"0x0\",\r\n    \"extraData\": \"0x\",\r\n    \"gasLimit\": \"0x1c9c380\",\r\n    \"gasUsed\": \"0x0\",\r\n    \"hash\": \"0x9b2d8194a70e9dc1d42f4630ae1bdb1fe0b9f73cc48792e4488d81b0ece404d3\",\r\n    \"logsBloom\": \"\",\r\n    \"miner\": \"0x721d3be5d26c271226c97b05b7802a4a18ec484f\",\r\n    \"mixHash\": \"0x91d38009114e7037a3c3d9787660330d45f31589301eed0a33d3ae5724e27f14\",\r\n    \"nonce\": \"0x0000000000000000\",\r\n    \"number\": \"0xedcde0\",\r\n    \"parentHash\": \"0x4eacb60ebdb2c00e189c2286d941ea8825cd5ffb5a7dfab9e1a8cf2ed1bf39a7\",\r\n    \"receiptsRoot\": \"0x56e81f171bcc55a6ff8345e692c0f86e5b48e01b996cadc001622fb5e363b421\",\r\n    \"sha3Uncles\": \"0x1dcc4de8dec75d7aab85b567b6ccd41ad312451b948a7413f0a142fd40d49347\",\r\n    \"size\": \"0x206\",\r\n    \"stateRoot\": \"0xfdd41e3f906b69210cbf259347fc0a45befaf6a2d40ce89d26b6d4dc40c0998f\",\r\n    \"timestamp\": \"0x632b90d3\",\r\n    \"totalDifficulty\": \"0xc70d815d562d3cfa955\",\r\n    \"transactions\": [],\r\n    \"transactionsRoot\": \"0x56e81f171bcc55a6ff8345e692c0f86e5b48e01b996cadc001622fb5e363b421\",\r\n    \"uncles\": []\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere, we see a miner.\r\n\r\nIn the past, `trace_block` would return the miner along with their reward for the block.\r\n\r\nSince the merge, there is no reward, but there is still a miner.\r\n\r\nI propose that `trace_block` continues to return the miner. Without this, in order to find \"every appearance of every address\" we need to make a separate call to the RPC for every block we process (we now have to call into `eth_getBlockByNumber` as well as `trace_block`). This nearly doubles the cost of querying a single block and slows down our processing significantly.\r\n\r\nSuggestion: re-constitute the code that used to generate the miner `action` and send it with a `rewardType` of something like `pos-miner` and a zero value reward.",
